Repeat history

Don Boyd

July 09, 2015

  • Pensions analysis
    • Investment returns
      • From the PPD
    • Market assets of pension funds
      • From the PPD - note that this is plan FY end data
      • From the FOF - note that this is CY end data, which would give different results from plan fy end data
    • Asset allocations of pension funds
      • From the ppd
        • Each asset class individually
        • Summary allocation to major asset classes by year
      • From the FOF
  • Tax analysis
    • Start by looking at the raw tax data, adjusted for inflation, for picture of what happened in/after last 2 recessions
  • Income tax base analysis
    • PIT - look at AGI, taxable income, then consider progressivity adjustments
      • How does federal taxable income compare to iit revenue collections?
  • Sales tax base analysis
    • Basic estimate
    • Estimated sales tax base, broader economy, and sales tax revenue, adjusted for inflation, FY basis
  • Other taxes
    • Trends in other taxes (corp income tax, motor fuel tax, cigarette tax, estate tax, various smaller taxes)
    • Construct other tax base - simply base on gdp growth
  • Develop a longer series of investment returns by asset class consistent with history
